{"name":"Pray","permission":{"default":0,"IJqIDe1c5JlxpePC":3},"type":"skill","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your ability to truly set aside your own ego and commune with a deity.</p>\n<p>You may use Pray in the following situations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>In lieu of a Cool Test to resist Psychology.</li>\n<li>In lieu of a Charm Test to influence a Character &mdash; or a crowd, if combined with the <em>Public Speaking</em> Talent &mdash; who is particularly religious.</li>\n<li>In lieu of an Intimidate Test to inspire Fear in a target who fears your God.</li>\n<li>In Combat to meditate and gain +1 Advantage, up to a maximum of Fellowship Bonus times.</li>\n<li>To receive a Little Prayer (see <strong>Warhammer Fantasy Roleplay 4th Edition</strong>, page 204) from one or more Gods you follow.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Pray Skill may be used by Characters with the <em>Bless (Divine Lore)</em> and <em>Invoke (Divine Lore) </em>Talents to gain more tangible divine intervention. For more on this, see <strong>Warhammer Fantasy Roleplay 4th Edition, Chapter 7: Religion &amp; Belief.</strong></p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"advanced":{"value":"bsc","type":"String"},"grouped":{"value":"noSpec","type":"String"},"characteristic":{"type":"String","label":"Characteristic","value":"fel"},"advances":{"type":"Number","label":"Advances","value":0},"total":{"type":"Number","label":"Total"},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-content/icons/skills/adv-skill-fel.png","_id":"zpwffeoRi4vn9Hk6"}
